==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Max Schuler|Max Schuler]] German physicist

===Noun===
'''[[Schuler]] [[pendulum]]'''

#{{physics}} Any pendulum having a [[period]] equal to that of a [[hypothetical]] pendulum whose length is equal to the [[Earth]]'s [[radius]] (84.4 minutes); its arm will remain locally [[vertical]] when the [[pivot]] is moved and is therefore the basis of [[navigational]] [[instrument]]s

